<br>
First the pickpocket skill resets extremly slowly.  In a decent group at my level and skill I'd be lucky to be able to attempt to pickpocket about 3x during the fight and that's if it's a long one :P~~  <br>
<br>
Second, welp , you can't be hitting the mob while attempting to pickpocket, as well you have to be within a certain range (damned close actually) of the mob to pickpocket.  Soooo - rogue evades and pickpockets ? Only if he's a complete ass and loves to die.  Pickpocketing and still being in such close range would nullify the aggro drop the rogue got from evading.  <br>
<br>
I can't speak for every rogue out there, but unless i'm grouped with a level 60 warrior with epics - I spend my entire time trying to lessen aggro not increase it so that my cleric doesn't have to keep rezzing me.  The last thing on my mind is to click a damned button to PP a mob when evade fails (or worked but aggro is still so high the mob won't switch targets).<br>
<br>
It's getting to be a trend for people to point fingers at rogues when they get a lousy drop rate.  Maybe you folks would like to learn how Pickpocket works first before even making a post that casts doubt on an entire class.<br>
<br>
Kae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umorchaint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morchaint</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/21/01 4:54:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues and pick-pocketing</span><hr size=1> I don't think I've ever seen a rare gem drop at lower exit. I'm given to believe that the drop rates there are just crap. Oh wait, I think I've seen carnellians and star rose quartz looted there a few times.<br>
